explanation: The original code initialized num with range(1, 10), so the digit 0 was never included in the set of candidate digits. As a result 0 could never be printed even if it did not appear in the input. I fixed the initialization to include 0 by using range(10).
fixed_code:
S = input()
num = set([i for i in range(10)])

for s in S:
    num.discard(int(s))

print(*num)
